{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"In the next 18 minutes, I'm going to take you on a journey."},{"time":3000,"text":"And it's a journey that you and I have been on for many years now,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and it began some 50 years ago, when humans first stepped off our planet."},{"time":14000,"text":"And in those 50 years, not only did we literally, physically set foot on the moon,"},{"time":21000,"text":"but we have dispatched robotic spacecraft to all the planets -- all eight of them --"},{"time":28000,"text":"and we have landed on asteroids, we have rendezvoused with comets,"},{"time":32000,"text":"and, at this point in time, we have a spacecraft on its way to Pluto,"},{"time":37000,"text":"the body formerly known as a planet."},{"time":40000,"text":"And all of these robotic missions are part of a bigger human journey:"},{"time":46000,"text":"a voyage to understand something, to get a sense of our cosmic place,"},{"time":53000,"text":"to understand something of our origins, and how Earth, our planet,"},{"time":58000,"text":"and we, living on it, came to be."}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"And of all the places in the solar system that we might go to"},{"time":63000,"text":"and search for answers to questions like this,"},{"time":67000,"text":"there's Saturn. And we have been to Saturn before --"},{"time":70000,"text":"we visited Saturn in the early 1980s --"},{"time":73000,"text":"but our investigations of Saturn have become far more in-depth in detail"},{"time":78000,"text":"since the Cassini spacecraft, traveling across interplanetary space"},{"time":82000,"text":"for seven years, glided into orbit around Saturn in the summer of 2004,"},{"time":88000,"text":"and became at that point the farthest robotic outpost"},{"time":91000,"text":"that humanity had ever established around the Sun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"Now, the Saturn system is a rich planetary system."},{"time":99000,"text":"It offers mystery, scientific insight and obviously splendor beyond compare,"},{"time":106000,"text":"and the investigation of this system has enormous cosmic reach."},{"time":110000,"text":"In fact, just studying the rings alone, we stand to learn a lot"},{"time":114000,"text":"about the discs of stars and gas that we call the spiral galaxies."},{"time":119000,"text":"And here's a beautiful picture of the Andromeda Nebula,"},{"time":121000,"text":"which is our closest, largest spiral galaxy to the Milky Way."},{"time":125000,"text":"And then, here's a beautiful composite of the Whirlpool Galaxy,"},{"time":128000,"text":"taken by the Hubble Space Telescope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130000,"text":"So the journey back to Saturn is really part of and is also a metaphor"},{"time":136000,"text":"for a much larger human voyage"},{"time":138000,"text":"to understand the interconnectedness of everything around us,"},{"time":142000,"text":"and also how humans fit into that picture."},{"time":145000,"text":"And it pains me that I can't tell you all that we have learned with Cassini."},{"time":152000,"text":"I can't show you all the beautiful pictures that we've taken"},{"time":155000,"text":"in the last two and a half years, because I simply don't have the time."},{"time":158000,"text":"So I'm going to concentrate on two of the most exciting stories"},{"time":162000,"text":"that have emerged out of this major exploratory expedition"},{"time":166000,"text":"that we are conducting around Saturn,"},{"time":168000,"text":"and have been for the past two and a half years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171000,"text":"Saturn is accompanied by a very large and diverse collection of moons."},{"time":175000,"text":"They range in size from a few kilometers across to as big across as the U.S."},{"time":180000,"text":"Most of the beautiful pictures we've taken of Saturn, in fact,"},{"time":183000,"text":"show Saturn in accompaniment with some of its moons. Here's Saturn with Dione,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and then, here's Saturn showing the rings edge-on,"},{"time":191000,"text":"showing you just how vertically thin they are, with the moon Enceladus."},{"time":195000,"text":"Now, two of the 47 moons that Saturn has are standouts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200000,"text":"And those are Titan and Enceladus. Titan is Saturn's largest moon,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and, until Cassini had arrived there,"},{"time":207000,"text":"was the largest single expanse of unexplored terrain"},{"time":211000,"text":"that we had remaining in our solar system."},{"time":215000,"text":"And it is a body that has long intrigued people who've watched the planets."},{"time":219000,"text":"It has a very large, thick atmosphere,"},{"time":223000,"text":"and in fact, its surface environment was believed to be"},{"time":227000,"text":"more like the environment we have here on the Earth,"},{"time":231000,"text":"or at least had in the past, than any other body in the solar system."},{"time":235000,"text":"Its atmosphere is largely molecular nitrogen, like you are breathing here in this room,"},{"time":240000,"text":"except that its atmosphere is suffused with"},{"time":242000,"text":"simple organic materials like methane and propane and ethane."},{"time":246000,"text":"And these molecules high up in the atmosphere of Titan"},{"time":249000,"text":"get broken down, and their products join together to make haze particles."},{"time":254000,"text":"This haze is ubiquitous. It's completely global and enveloping Titan."},{"time":259000,"text":"And that's why you cannot see down to the surface"},{"time":262000,"text":"with our eyes in the visible region of the spectrum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264000,"text":"But these haze particles, it was surmised,"},{"time":267000,"text":"before we got there with Cassini, over billions and billions of years,"},{"time":271000,"text":"gently drifted down to the surface and coated the surface"},{"time":275000,"text":"in a thick organic sludge."},{"time":276000,"text":"So like the equivalent, the Titan equivalent, of tar, or oil, or what -- we didn't know what."},{"time":283000,"text":"But this is what we suspected. And these molecules,"},{"time":285000,"text":"especially methane and ethane, can be liquids at the surface temperatures of Titan."},{"time":294000,"text":"And so it turns out that methane is to Titan what water is to the Earth."},{"time":299000,"text":"It's a condensable in the atmosphere,"},{"time":301000,"text":"and so recognizing this circumstance brought to the fore"},{"time":306000,"text":"a whole world of bizarre possibilities. You can have methane clouds, OK,"},{"time":311000,"text":"and above those clouds, you have this hundreds of kilometers of haze,"},{"time":314000,"text":"which prevent any sunlight from getting to the surface."},{"time":316000,"text":"The temperature at the surface is some 350 degrees below zero Fahrenheit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322000,"text":"But despite that cold, you could have rain falling down on the surface of Titan."},{"time":328000,"text":"And doing on Titan what rain does on the Earth: it carves gullies; it forms rivers"},{"time":331000,"text":"and cataracts; it can create canyons; it can pool in large basins and craters."},{"time":338000,"text":"It can wash the sludge off high mountain peaks and hills,"},{"time":341000,"text":"down into the lowlands. So stop and think for a minute."},{"time":344000,"text":"Try to imagine what the surface of Titan might look like."},{"time":348000,"text":"It's dark. High noon on Titan is as dark as deep earth twilight on the Earth."},{"time":353000,"text":"It's cold, it's eerie, it's misty,"},{"time":355000,"text":"it might be raining, and you might be standing"},{"time":358000,"text":"on the shores of Lake Michigan brimming with paint thinner. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"That is the view that we had of the surface of Titan before we got there with Cassini, \n"},{"time":367000,"text":"and I can tell you that what we have found on Titan, though it is not the same in detail,"},{"time":374000,"text":"is every bit as fascinating as that story is."},{"time":377000,"text":"And for us, it has been like -- the Cassini people --"},{"time":379000,"text":"it has been like a Jules Verne adventure come true."},{"time":383000,"text":"As I said, it has a thick, extensive atmosphere."},{"time":385000,"text":"This is a picture of Titan, backlit by the Sun, with the rings as a beautiful backdrop."},{"time":390000,"text":"And yet another moon there --"},{"time":392000,"text":"I don't even know which one it is. It's a very extensive atmosphere."},{"time":395000,"text":"We have instruments on Cassini which can see down to the surface"},{"time":398000,"text":"through this atmosphere, and my camera system is one of them."},{"time":402000,"text":"And we have taken pictures like this."},{"time":404000,"text":"And what you see is bright and dark regions, and that's about as far as it got for us."},{"time":409000,"text":"It was so mystifying: we couldn't make out what we were seeing on Titan."},{"time":413000,"text":"When you look closer at this region, you start to see things"},{"time":418000,"text":"like sinuous channels -- we didn't know. You see a few round things."},{"time":422000,"text":"This, we later found out, is, in fact, a crater,"},{"time":424000,"text":"but there are very few craters on the surface of Titan,"},{"time":427000,"text":"meaning it's a very young surface."},{"time":429000,"text":"And there are features that look tectonic."},{"time":431000,"text":"They look like they've been pulled apart."},{"time":433000,"text":"Whenever you see anything linear on a planet,"},{"time":435000,"text":"it means there's been a fracture, like a fault."},{"time":439000,"text":"And so it's been tectonically altered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":441000,"text":"But we couldn't make sense of our images,"},{"time":443000,"text":"until, six months after we got into orbit,"},{"time":447000,"text":"an event occurred that many have regarded"},{"time":449000,"text":"as the highlight of Cassini's investigation of Titan."},{"time":452000,"text":"And that was the deployment of the Huygens probe,"},{"time":455000,"text":"the European-built Huygens probe that Cassini had carried"},{"time":458000,"text":"for seven years across the solar system. We deployed it to the atmosphere of Titan,"},{"time":462000,"text":"it took two and a half hours to descend, and it landed on the surface."},{"time":466000,"text":"And I just want to emphasize how significant an event this is."},{"time":470000,"text":"This is a device of human making,"},{"time":473000,"text":"and it landed in the outer solar system for the first time in human history."},{"time":477000,"text":"It is so significant that, in my mind,"},{"time":481000,"text":"this was an event that should have been celebrated"},{"time":483000,"text":"with ticker tape parades in every city across the U.S. and Europe,"},{"time":488000,"text":"and sadly, that wasn't the case."},{"time":490000,"text":"(Laughter)."}]},{"cues":[{"time":492000,"text":"It was significant for another reason. This is an international mission,"},{"time":495000,"text":"and this event was celebrated in Europe, in Germany,"},{"time":498000,"text":"and the celebratory presentations were given in English accents,"},{"time":502000,"text":"and American accents, and German accents, and French and Italian and Dutch accents."},{"time":508000,"text":"It was a moving demonstration of what the words"},{"time":512000,"text":"\"united nations\" are supposed to mean:"},{"time":514000,"text":"a true union of nations joined together in a colossal effort for good."},{"time":520000,"text":"And, in this case, it was a massive undertaking to explore a planet,"},{"time":524000,"text":"and to come to understand a planetary system"},{"time":527000,"text":"that, for all of human history, had been unreachable,"},{"time":531000,"text":"and now humans had actually touched it."},{"time":533000,"text":"So it was -- I mean, I'm getting goose bumps just talking about it."},{"time":537000,"text":"It was a tremendously emotional event,"},{"time":539000,"text":"and it's something that I will personally never forget, and you shouldn't either."},{"time":544000,"text":"(Applause)."}]},{"cues":[{"time":550000,"text":"But anyway, the probe took measurements of the atmosphere on the way down,"},{"time":553000,"text":"and it also took panoramic pictures."},{"time":555000,"text":"And I can't tell you what it was like to see the first pictures"},{"time":559000,"text":"of Titan's surface from the probe. And this is what we saw."},{"time":563000,"text":"And it was a shocker, because it was everything we wanted"},{"time":566000,"text":"those other pictures taken from orbit to be."},{"time":568000,"text":"It was an unambiguous pattern, a geological pattern."},{"time":572000,"text":"It's a dendritic drainage pattern that can be formed only by the flow of liquids."},{"time":577000,"text":"And you can follow these channels"},{"time":579000,"text":"and you can see how they all converge."},{"time":580000,"text":"And they converge into this channel here, which drains into this region."},{"time":584000,"text":"You are looking at a shoreline."},{"time":586000,"text":"Was this a shoreline of fluids? We didn't know."},{"time":589000,"text":"But this is somewhat of a shoreline."}]},{"cues":[{"time":591000,"text":"This picture is taken at 16 kilometers."},{"time":593000,"text":"This is the picture taken at eight kilometers, OK? Again, the shoreline."},{"time":597000,"text":"Okay, now, 16 kilometers, eight kilometers -- this is roughly an airline altitude."},{"time":602000,"text":"If you were going to take an airplane trip across the U.S.,"},{"time":605000,"text":"you would be flying at these altitudes."},{"time":607000,"text":"So, this is the picture you would have at the window of Titanian Airlines"},{"time":611000,"text":"as you fly across the surface of Titan. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":614000,"text":"And then finally, the probe came to rest on the surface,"},{"time":618000,"text":"and I'm going to show you, ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":620000,"text":"the first picture ever taken from the surface of a moon in the outer solar system."},{"time":624000,"text":"And here is the horizon, OK?"},{"time":628000,"text":"These are probably water ice pebbles, yes?"},{"time":632000,"text":"(Applause)."},{"time":637000,"text":"And obviously, it landed in one of these flat, dark regions"},{"time":641000,"text":"and it didn't sink out of sight. So it wasn't fluid that we landed in."},{"time":646000,"text":"What the probe came down in was basically"},{"time":649000,"text":"the Titan equivalent of a mud flat."},{"time":652000,"text":"This is an unconsolidated ground that is suffused with liquid methane."},{"time":657000,"text":"And it's probably the case that this material"},{"time":660000,"text":"has washed off the highlands of Titan"},{"time":664000,"text":"through these channels that we saw,"},{"time":665000,"text":"and has drained over billions of years to fill in low-lying basins."},{"time":669000,"text":"And that is what the Huygens probe landed in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":672000,"text":"But still, there was no sign in our images,"},{"time":676000,"text":"or even in the Huygens' images, of any large, open bodies of fluids."},{"time":681000,"text":"Where were they? It got even more puzzling when we found dunes."},{"time":686000,"text":"OK, so this is our movie of the equatorial region of Titan,"},{"time":689000,"text":"showing these dunes. These are dunes that are 100 meters tall,"},{"time":692000,"text":"separated by a few kilometers,"},{"time":695000,"text":"and they go on for miles and miles and miles."},{"time":698000,"text":"There's hundreds, up to a 1,000 or 1,200 miles of dunes."},{"time":701000,"text":"This is the Saharan desert of Titan."},{"time":704000,"text":"It's obviously a place which is very dry, or you wouldn't get dunes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709000,"text":"So again, it got puzzling that there were no bodies of fluid,"},{"time":714000,"text":"until finally, we saw lakes in the polar regions."},{"time":718000,"text":"And there is a lake scene in the south polar region of Titan."},{"time":722000,"text":"It's about the size of Lake Ontario."},{"time":724000,"text":"And then, only a week and a half ago,"},{"time":725000,"text":"we flew over the north pole of Titan and found, again,"},{"time":729000,"text":"we found a feature here the size of the Caspian Sea."},{"time":734000,"text":"So it seems that the liquids, for some reason we don't understand,"},{"time":738000,"text":"or during at least this season, are apparently at the poles of Titan."},{"time":743000,"text":"And I think you would agree that we have found Titan"},{"time":746000,"text":"is a remarkable, mystical place. It's exotic, it's alien, but yet strangely Earth-like,"},{"time":753000,"text":"and having Earth-like geological formations"},{"time":756000,"text":"and a tremendous geographical diversity,"},{"time":760000,"text":"and is a fascinating world whose only rival in the solar system"},{"time":764000,"text":"for complexity and richness is the Earth itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767000,"text":"And so now we go onto Enceladus. Enceladus is a small moon,"},{"time":772000,"text":"it's about a tenth the size of Titan. And you can see it here next to England,"},{"time":776000,"text":"just to show you the size. This is not meant to be a threat."},{"time":779000,"text":"(Laughter)."},{"time":781000,"text":"And Enceladus is very white, it's very bright,"},{"time":785000,"text":"and its surface is obviously wrecked with fractures."},{"time":789000,"text":"It is a very geologically active body."},{"time":791000,"text":"But the mother lode of discoveries on Enceladus"},{"time":793000,"text":"was found at the south pole -- and we're looking at the south pole here --"},{"time":796000,"text":"where we found this system of fractures."},{"time":799000,"text":"And they're a different color because they're a different composition."},{"time":801000,"text":"They are coated. These fractures are coated with organic materials."},{"time":806000,"text":"Moreover, this whole, entire region, the south polar region,"},{"time":810000,"text":"has elevated temperatures. It's the hottest place on the planet, on the body."},{"time":814000,"text":"That's as bizarre as finding that the Antarctic on the Earth is hotter than the tropics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":819000,"text":"And then, when we took additional pictures, we discovered"},{"time":822000,"text":"that from these fractures are issuing jets of fine, icy particles"},{"time":828000,"text":"extending hundreds of miles into space."},{"time":830000,"text":"And when we color-code this image, to bring out the faint light levels,"},{"time":833000,"text":"we see that these jets feed a plume"},{"time":837000,"text":"that, in fact, we see, in other images, goes thousands of miles"},{"time":841000,"text":"into the space above Enceladus."},{"time":843000,"text":"My team and I have examined images like this,"},{"time":846000,"text":"and like this one, and have thought about the other results from Cassini."},{"time":850000,"text":"And we have arrived at the conclusion"},{"time":854000,"text":"that these jets may be erupting from pockets"},{"time":857000,"text":"of liquid water under the surface of Enceladus."}]},{"cues":[{"time":861000,"text":"So we have, possibly, liquid water, organic materials and excess heat."},{"time":866000,"text":"In other words, we have possibly stumbled upon"},{"time":869000,"text":"the holy grail of modern day planetary exploration,"},{"time":873000,"text":"or in other words, an environment that is potentially suitable for living organisms."},{"time":877000,"text":"And I don't think I need to tell you that the discovery of life"},{"time":880000,"text":"elsewhere in our solar system,"},{"time":882000,"text":"whether it be on Enceladus or elsewhere,"},{"time":884000,"text":"would have enormous cultural and scientific implications."},{"time":887000,"text":"Because if we could demonstrate that genesis had occurred"},{"time":891000,"text":"not once, but twice, independently, in our solar system,"},{"time":895000,"text":"then that means, by inference, it has occurred a staggering number of times"},{"time":899000,"text":"throughout the universe and its 13.7 billion year history."}]},{"cues":[{"time":904000,"text":"Right now, Earth is the only planet still that we know is teeming with life."},{"time":908000,"text":"It is precious, it is unique,"},{"time":911000,"text":"it is still, so far, the only home we've ever known."},{"time":914000,"text":"And if any of you were alert and coherent during the 1960s --"},{"time":921000,"text":"and we'd forgive you, if you weren't, OK --"},{"time":923000,"text":"you would remember this very famous picture"},{"time":925000,"text":"taken by the Apollo 8 astronauts in 1968."},{"time":929000,"text":"It was the first time that Earth was imaged from space,"},{"time":932000,"text":"and it had an enormous impact on our sense of place in the universe,"},{"time":935000,"text":"and our sense of responsibility for the protection of our own planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940000,"text":"Well, we on Cassini have taken an equivalent first,"},{"time":944000,"text":"a picture that no human eye has ever seen before."},{"time":948000,"text":"It is a total eclipse of the Sun, seen from the other side of Saturn."},{"time":952000,"text":"And in this impossibly beautiful picture,"},{"time":956000,"text":"you see the main rings backlit by the Sun,"},{"time":958000,"text":"you see the refracted image of the Sun"},{"time":961000,"text":"and you see this ring created, in fact,"},{"time":963000,"text":"by the exhalations of Enceladus."},{"time":966000,"text":"But as if that weren't brilliant enough, we can spot, in this beautiful image,"},{"time":972000,"text":"sight of our own planet,"},{"time":974000,"text":"cradled in the arms of Saturn's rings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978000,"text":"Now, there is something deeply moving"},{"time":980000,"text":"about seeing ourselves from afar,"},{"time":982000,"text":"and capturing the sight of our little, blue-ocean planet"},{"time":985000,"text":"in the skies of other worlds."},{"time":987000,"text":"And that, and the perspective of ourselves that we gain from that,"},{"time":991000,"text":"may be, in the end, the finest reward that we earn"},{"time":995000,"text":"from this journey of discovery that started half a century ago."},{"time":998000,"text":"And thank you very much."},{"time":1000000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}